<paragraph id="8BC93685DB626352ECBA0CC1FEF0FB11" blockId="6.[151,1436,1184,2031]" box="[151,288,1184,1210]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC93685DB626352ECEB0CA4FB17FA31" blockId="6.[151,1436,1184,2031]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Length: male 
<quantity id="4C8E9B60DB626352ED440CA4FE67FB74" box="[361,439,1221,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="12.0">12mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity id="4C8E9B60DB626352EE370CA4FDB8FB74" box="[538,616,1221,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="13.0">13mm</quantity>
; body moderately convex in profile, length c. 3x height. Variegated in metallic blue, red, yellow and brown: (i) anterior of head, head appendages, legs, basal half of middle of pronotum, scutellum, basal third of elytral suture and 6 spots on each elytron (beside scutellum, near suture 1/ 3 from base, on humerus, behind humerus, near side 1/2 from base, near side ¾ from base), black to blackishbrown, with dark blue reflection; (ii) remainder of elytra yellow; (iii) remainder of prothorax, mesoventrite, middle of metaventrite and base of trochanters red to reddish-yellow; (iv) abdomen brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC93685DB626352ECEB0DC4FB54F96F" blockId="6.[151,1436,1184,2031]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
